Not ready to Apply?








                        Job Description
                    


  At Albemarle, we’ve built a thriving international business by envisioning a limitless future and putting innovation to work to improve people’s lives. That’s our culture. That’s our commitment. And when you join our team, it’s an opportunity you share with talented men and women around the globe. Anyone can give you a job. At Albemarle, we believe you deserve more. Something big enough to build a future. Big enough to change the world.   Job Description  As a Process Development Engineer, you are leading projects to scale up products or processes to commercial plant production scale. Our products range from state-of-the-art catalysts for the petrochemical industry to engineered inorganic substances for various applications. Our processes range from unit operations to complete production plant lines.  Responsibilities  Pilot scale development of new catalysts for different applications (e.g. Hydroprocessing and Fluid Catalytic Cracking). Extending our process technology knowledge in extrusion, impregnation, drying, physical transport phenomena and modeling. Set up and execute experimental campaigns using Design of Experiment. Leading plant trials for new products and/or new production processes. Development of innovative process steps and introduction of new technology. Interface between R&D, analytical and plant technology departments in order to develop and transfer product and process knowhow.  Supporting the plant in troubleshooting manufacturing issues and process related excursions. Identify innovative technology that will improve the quality and cost of products and processes.   Job requirements  Master or PhD degree in Chemical Engineering. Relevant work experience or a PDEng degree is a plus. Interest in process technology and physical transport phenomena. Affinity with R&D and process equipment. Proactive, convincing and decisive; Flexible and stress resistant; Analytical, solution-driven and pragmatic; Good communication skills. Strong knowledge of application of statistical techniques for data analysis, process control, and validation. Strong laboratory skills; hands-on mindset. Good understanding of Design of Experiments, with proven ability to apply within chemical operations. Good knowledge of problem solving & root cause analysis methodologies. Fluent English, Good knowledge of Dutch.    Responsibilities:  Experience:  Education:Doctorate: Chemical Engineering, Masters: Chemical Engineering (Required) Certification:  Skills:  Language:Dutch (Required), English (Required) 






